Transformer Model with CUDA
A lightweight transformer model with custom CUDA kernels for grouped query attention and mixture of experts (MoE), built using PyTorch Lightning.
Features
- Transformer with grouped query attention and MoE
- CUDA-accelerated operations (`transformer_cuda.cu`)
- Key-value caching for efficient inference
- Tests for overfitting, KV cache, and variable inputs
- PyTorch Lightning for streamlined training


git clone https://github.com/your-username/transformer-cuda.git
cd transformer-cuda

Install dependencies:
bash

python -m venv ligth
source ligth/bin/activate
pip install torch==2.0.1+cu118 pytorch-lightning==2.0.0 ninja

Compile CUDA extension:
bash

export TORCH_CUDA_ARCH_LIST="7.5"
python setup.py install

Usage
Train:
bash

python transformer_model.py

Test:
bash

python test_model.py

